{
  "texts": [
    "We start by answering the basic question of whether judges who attend economics training actually use the language of economics in their opinions.",
    "We look at the vector similarity of a case to a lexicon of economics language in word embedding space, as described in Subsection 3.2 above.",
    "The sample includes majority-opinion authors and excludes non-author panel members.",
    "Figure 3 reports the event study for the economics embedding similarity.",
    "Formally, the markers give the point estimates for γk from Equation (2), with 95% condence intervals computed using the associated standard errors (clustered by judge)."
  ]
}